  <body id="msgFeedSummaryBody" selected="false">
    <p>We have a great tradition of extended sprints around big Drupal events including the ones we did around DrupalCons in Portland, Munich, Denver, as well as Drupal Dev Days like Dublin and Barcelona. While there is a sprint day included in DrupalCons (usually) on Friday, given that a lot of the Drupal core and contrib developers fly in for these events, it makes a lot of sense to use this opportunity to start sooner and/or extend our stay and work together in one space on the harder problems.</p>
<p><a href="http://prague2013.drupal.org/">DrupalCon Prague</a> is next up! This is the first DrupalCon, where the Drupal Association recognises the need for extended sprints as part of the schedule and works with sprinters to provide space on Monday as well! We are still organising additional weekend sprints before/after for ourselves! There are already various sprints signed up including <em>Multilingual, Views, WSCCI, Configuration management and Fields</em> all to further development of Drupal 8 at various capacities on these weekends. Now is the time to consider if you can be available and book your travel and hotel accordingly!</p>
<div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2em;"><img src="https://groups.drupal.org/files/Hub-panorama-optimized.jpg" alt="" />Hub Praha - our weekend sprint space. Nice, right?</div>
<div style="border: 1em solid #ffffcc; padding: 1em; margin-bottom: 2em;">
<h3 class="content">Practical details</h3>
<dl>
<dt>Dates</dt>
<dd>21st (Sat), 22nd (Sun), 23rd (Mon) of Sept and the 28th (Sat) and 29th (Sun) of Sept 2013. (There is already a DrupalCon sprint day on the 27th at the DrupalCon venue as well).</dd>
<dt>Times</dt>
<dd>We start each day at 9am and have space booked until late in the night as needed (at least on the weekends).</dd>
<dt>Locations</dt>
<dd>
<ul>
<li><strong>Weekend before DrupalCon</strong>: <a href="https://www.google.hu/maps/preview#!data=!1m4!1m3!1d2761!2d14.402251!3d50.076391!4m25!2m11!1m10!1s0x0%3A0x2068c37eab9b5371!3m8!1m3!1d43016!2d19.1373505!3d47.6359439!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!5m12!1m11!1sHub+Praha!4m8!1m3!1d43016!2d19.1373505!3d47.6359439!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!17b1">Hub Praha; Drtinova 557/10; 150 00 Praha 5-Smíchov</a> easily accessible with light public transport from the DrupalCon venue.</li>
<li><strong>Monday (DrupalCon training day):</strong> The DrupalCon venue, room to be specified later.</li>
<li><strong>Session days (Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday)</strong>: DrupalCon provided coder lounge space</li>
<li><strong>Friday (DrupalCon official sprint day)</strong>: <a href="https://prague2013.drupal.org/program/sprints">DrupalCon provides sprinting space</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Weekend after DrupalCon</strong>: <a href="https://www.google.hu/maps/preview#!data=!1m4!1m3!1d2761!2d14.402251!3d50.076391!4m25!2m11!1m10!1s0x0%3A0x2068c37eab9b5371!3m8!1m3!1d43016!2d19.1373505!3d47.6359439!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!5m12!1m11!1sHub+Praha!4m8!1m3!1d43016!2d19.1373505!3d47.6359439!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!17b1">Hub Praha; Drtinova 557/10; 150 00 Praha 5-Smíchov</a> easily accessible with light public transport from the DrupalCon venue.</li>
</ul>
